benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: PUT /1.0/kb/accounts/{accountId}/customFields - Modify custom fields to account

covered: Valid Request coverage: TC01, TC02, TC03, TC04, TC15, TC16, TC17, TC24, TC25, TC28 (204 responses and updates)
Error handling coverage: TC06, TC07, TC08, TC09, TC10, TC11, TC12, TC18, TC20, TC21 (400/401/400/400/400/400/400) etc.
Header validation and optional headers: TC02 (optional headers), TC05 (unsupported headers ignored)
Edge cases coverage: TC15 (empty array), TC16 (max field values), TC17 (extra properties ignored), TC23 (duplicate field names), TC24 (backward compatibility)
Integration and side effects: TC27 (audit logs), TC28 (external reporting)
gaps: Pagination handling for large data sets (not applicable to PUT here, but guideline mentions it for listing scenarios)
Rate limiting / throttling tests (no test simulates burst requests)
Caching behavior / ETag handling (no tests around caching headers)
Unauthorized access beyond 401 case (no explicit 403 scenario for insufficient permissions)
Server error handling beyond 503 (no 500 Internal Server Error scenario)
Non-existing resource update race conditions or concurrency edge cases beyond TC25 (no explicit race-condition tests for same-resource edits)
Detailed validation messages for each specific invalid field (some tests generic 400s, not always granular)
recommendations: Add a dedicated test for 403 Forbidden to cover authorization with insufficient permissions
Add a 500 Internal Server Error scenario to validate server failure handling
Introduce rate limiting / throttle tests to ensure proper handling under high load
Add caching-related tests (ETag/Cache-Control) for PUT responses
Expand concurrency tests to explicitly cover race conditions on the same account.customFields resource
Enhance TC18/TC20/TC21 to assert specific invalid input details in the response body
Add explicit 413 vs 204 behavior test in TC26 with clear payload size threshold
Include explicit test for partial update rejection if unsupported by API semantics
Ensure 403 scenario when authentication token is present but lacks required scope
